{"ops":[{"insert":"Preheat oven to 190 degree C.

Line a 38 cm x 25 cm jelly roll pan with parchment paper.
"}]}

{"ops":[{"insert":"Separate egg yolks and whites into two bowls.

Keep egg whites in the refrigerator, and the egg yolk at room temperature.
"}]}

{"ops":[{"insert":"Add half of sugar and whisk until egg mixture becomes double in volume.

When you lift the whisk into the air with some of the mixture on it, the mixture should fall back into the bowl in ribbons, which slowly disappear back into the mixture.
"}]}

{"ops":[{"insert":"Gently whisk a 1/3 egg whites into the egg yolk mixture until incorporated.

Then add back to the egg whites.
"}]}

{"ops":[{"insert":"When the cake is completely cool, combine the heavy cream, sugar, and matcha powder in a large bowl.

Beat until firm and spreadable, so it won’t ooze out of the cake when you’re rolling it up.
"}]}
